OL,3,CHeat to rise to possible record-
OL,4,Cbreaking highs over rest of bank
OL,5,Choliday weekend
OL,7,FTemperatures will continue to climb
OL,8,Fthroughout the weekend, as forecasters
OL,9,Fsaid the "exceptional heat" may break
OL,10,Frecords for the warmest day in May and
OL,11,Fhottest bank holiday.
OL,13,FThe UK saw the hottest day of the year
OL,14,Fso far on Saturday when the village of
OL,15,FFrittenden, in Kent, hit 30.5C.
OL,17,FIt was the first time this year that
OL,18,Fthe UK had passed 30C. The last time
OL,19,Fthat happened in May was in 2012.
OL,26,@qD@JOUqD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
