OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1779718268
OL,3,CHeat to rise to possible record-
OL,4,Cbreaking highs over rest of bank
OL,5,Choliday weekend
OL,7,FBut temperatures are expected to rise
OL,8,Feven further on Sunday, with highs of
OL,9,F31C predicted in the South East, and
OL,10,Feven further on Monday, when potential
OL,11,Fpeaks of between 33C and 34C are
OL,12,Fpossible.
OL,14,FRecords could be broken for the
OL,15,Fhottest May day in the UK and England,
OL,16,Fcurrently 32.8C; the hottest May day
OL,17,Fin Wales, currently 30.6C; as well as
OL,18,Fthe UK and England's hottest bank
OL,19,Fholiday, which sits for now at 33.3C.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
