OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1779718268
OL,3,CHeat to rise to possible record-
OL,4,Cbreaking highs over rest of bank
OL,5,Choliday weekend
OL,7,F"If we hit that 33C, maybe even
OL,8,Flocally close towards 34C, that would
OL,9,Fbring us our hottest bank holiday day
OL,10,Fon record, as well as our hottest day
OL,11,Fin May on record, so it really is
OL,12,Fquite exceptional heat that is
OL,13,Fbuilding for the time of year."
OL,15,FThe UK Health Security Agency (UKHSA)
OL,16,Fissued amber heat health alerts on
OL,17,FFriday morning for the East Midlands,
OL,18,FWest Midlands, the East of England,
OL,19,FLondon and the South East.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
