CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1779718268
OL,3,CHeat to rise to possible record-
OL,4,Cbreaking highs over rest of bank
OL,5,Choliday weekend
OL,7,FThe alerts will remain in place until
OL,8,F5pm on Wednesday and replace less
OL,9,Fsevere yellow alerts, which were
OL,10,Fpreviously issued.
OL,12,FThe alerts mean there is likely to be
OL,13,F"a rise in deaths, particularly among
OL,14,Fthose aged 65 and over or with health
OL,15,Fconditions" and increased demand on
OL,16,Fall health and social care services,
OL,17,Faccording to the UKHSA website.
OL,19,FYellow alerts have been issued for the
OL,20,FNorth East and North West, Yorkshire
OL,21,Fand Humber, and the South West.
OL,26,@uD@AOUwD@KO]
